			<h1 style="margin-bottom: -48px;"> <%= notice %> </h1>
		<% end %>

		<h1> Valerie Vaughn </h2>
		<h3 style="text-decoration: underline;"> Me in 10 seconds </h3>
		<p>
		“You must do the things you think you cannot do.” <br>
		 ~Eleanor Roosevelt
		</p> <br>

		<h3 style="text-decoration: underline;"> Posts <h3>
		<p class="title_of_work" onclick='show_piece("piece_zero");'> The Flight of Succubus </p>
		<p class="title_of_work" onclick='show_piece("piece_one");'> Home </p>
		<p class="title_of_work" onclick='show_piece("piece_two");'> The Quiet Survival of Loneliness </p>
		<p class="title_of_work" onclick='show_piece("piece_three");'> Armchair Wallflower </p>
		<p class="title_of_work" onclick='show_piece("piece_four");'> Love Burns </p>
		<p class="title_of_work" onclick='show_piece("piece_five");'> The Death of Love </p> 
		<p class="title_of_work" onclick='show_piece("piece_six");'> This Place </p>
		<p class="title_of_work" onclick='show_piece("piece_seven");'> Birth </p>
	</div>


	<div class="piece_of_work" id="piece_zero">
		<h1 onclick='show_default("piece_zero")' class="go_back_btn">
			<i class="fas fa-arrow-left" style="margin-right: 3px;"></i> Go Back 
		</h1>
		<h3 class="piece_header"> The Flight of Succubus </h3>		
		<p>
Bound together,
<br> <br>
since torn apart.
<br> <br>
Once a proud smirk,
<br> <br>
now gone.
<br> <br>
Staged love,
<br> <br>
unnatural grin.
<br> <br>
Poison lips,
<br> <br>
drink memories down.
<br> <br>
Succubus flight,
<br> <br>
succumbs to night.
		</p>
	</div>


	<div class="piece_of_work" id="piece_one">
		<h1 onclick='show_default("piece_one")' class="go_back_btn">
			<i class="fas fa-arrow-left" style="margin-right: 3px;"></i> Go Back 
		</h1>
		<h3 class="piece_header"> Home </h3>		
		<p>
A winding Virginia road.<br>
An old country back road. <br>
A road which leads me, <br>
Home.
<br> <br>
Past everlasting trees. <br>
Past pastures of manure, <br>
Coloring each a deep green; <br>
Weathered wooden fences, <br>
Guide me, on my way, <br>
Home.
<br> <br>
Mountains so high, <br>
Surely I can reach their unbound skies. <br>
Skies which surround the place <br>
I call, <br>
Home.
<br> <br>
Deep blue ponds. <br>
Fishing hole fools. <br>
Talking about the one that got away, <br>
On our way, <br>
Home.
<br> <br>
Back to a place, <br>
My space. <br>
A place where I am free, <br>
Free to be me. <br>
The place I call, <br>
Home.
		</p>
	</div>


	<div class="piece_of_work" id="piece_two">
		<h1 onclick='show_default("piece_two")' class="go_back_btn">
			<i class="fas fa-arrow-left" style="margin-right: 3px;"></i> Go Back 
		</h1>
		<h3 class="piece_header"> The Quiet Survival of Lonelines </h3>		
		<p>
Our empty flat, in which I sit,
<br> <br>
feels like night even when it’s day.
<br> <br>
All my days seem like nights since we parted ways.
<br> <br>
The early morning winter winds blow negativity aside,
<br> <br>
there’s already five inches of snow on the ground
<br> <br>
with more headed in a direction which I must escape;
<br> <br>
I must make my way before I convince my mind to stay.
<br> <br>
I drive in the direction of a new life
<br> <br>
barely escaping my own holocaust life,
<br> <br>
my mental needle closely rests on empty,
<br> <br>
I try not run out of gas before I get out what’s inside my head,
<br> <br>
how quickly your love ran to another
<br> <br>
as the quiet survival of loneliness fuels me ahead.
		</p>
	</div>


	<div class="piece_of_work" id="piece_three">
		<h1 onclick='show_default("piece_three")' class="go_back_btn">
			<i class="fas fa-arrow-left" style="margin-right: 3px;"></i> Go Back 
		</h1>
		<h3 class="piece_header"> Armchair Wallflower </h3>		
		<p>
I sit up, <br>
against the chair back, <br>
as the lies stack <br>
against me, <br>
I try not to fold <br>
from the weight <br>
of words, <br>
be bold, <br>
I am told <br>
to find the courage <br>
not to lose strength, <br>
at times <br>
to lost to walk <br>
to broken to surrender, <br>
finding no truth <br>
in the falsehood of others.
		</p>
	</div>


	<div class="piece_of_work" id="piece_four">
		<h1 onclick='show_default("piece_four")' class="go_back_btn">
			<i class="fas fa-arrow-left" style="margin-right: 3px;"></i> Go Back 
		</h1>
		<h3 class="piece_header"> Love Burns </h3>		
		<p>
Your blistery words
<br> <br>
spoke only to gain ground,
<br> <br>
your breath burns
<br> <br>
like embers of a wildfire,
<br> <br>
I try to extinguish you,
<br> <br>
the heat of dying flames
<br> <br>
burn me
<br> <br>
burn us.
<br> <br>
The last flicker of our souls give way,
<br> <br>
a passion soot remains,
<br> <br>
we drift softly into an embrace
<br> <br>
only to burn one another
<br> <br>
with our dying flame.
		</p>
	</div>


	<div class="piece_of_work" id="piece_five">
		<h1 onclick='show_default("piece_five")' class="go_back_btn">
			<i class="fas fa-arrow-left" style="margin-right: 3px;"></i> Go Back 
		</h1>
		<h3 class="piece_header"> The Death of Love </h3>		
		<p>
I often wonder how different my life would have been <br> <br>
had my mother not died when I was twenty-seven.<br> <br>
Would my series of life mistakes even exist beyond just a bad dream;<br> <br>
each a testament to my inability to chose wisely free of an inebriated state.<br> <br>
Several bad decisions away, one ending with a ring on my left hand<br> <br>
leading to false accusations and label lies.<br> <br>
Time does not heal, that is a bullshit lie.<br> <br>
Time does not lessen the pain of life.<br> <br>
Time is never on one’s side, least of all mine.<br> <br>
Silence slices the deafness of uncaring ears<br> <br>
as each is not what the other one thought<br> <br>
lost to uncompromising pride<br> <br>
as once loved expectations die.
		</p>
	</div>


	<div class="piece_of_work" id="piece_six">
		<h1 onclick='show_default("piece_six")' class="go_back_btn">
			<i class="fas fa-arrow-left" style="margin-right: 3px;"></i> Go Back 
		</h1>
		<h3 class="piece_header"> This Place </h3>		
		<p>
This Place
<br> <br>
All your life,
<br> <br>
you wanted to be
<br> <br>
someplace else.
<br> <br>
Now you are there
<br> <br>
and you don’t know
<br> <br>
what to do
<br> <br>
with yourself.
<br> <br>
So you sit and stare
<br> <br>
into the bottom of
<br> <br>
a half-empty glass,
<br> <br>
in hopes to catch a glance
<br> <br>
of a life to live for.
		</p>
	</div>


	<div class="piece_of_work" id="piece_seven">
		<h1 onclick='show_default("piece_seven")' class="go_back_btn">
			<i class="fas fa-arrow-left" style="margin-right: 3px;"></i> Go Back 
		</h1>
		<h3 class="piece_header"> Birth </h3>		
		<p>
I was born two weeks overdue, <br>
still early in life. <br>
More time was needed in my mother’s womb, <br>
more time to feel complete, <br>
More time was needed in my mother’s womb, <br>
and told to land on my feet. <br>
Face forward <br>
while the sting of the world whips me into its desired shape, <br>
shift-changing, clock awakening <br>
sunrise schedules my time to fit the workday <br>
to type my day away for minimal pay <br>
in a one percent society which does not represent me, <br>
but likes to micro-manage me. <br>
Time clock, punch-management <br>
inaccurate directions impede my stride, <br> 
retracting dreams from attainable echelon skies; <br>
I rise not from sleep but from a deep understanding <br>
as tides of fluid birth nourish my seed of growth. <br>
I plant my feet firmly upon the soil of my soul, <br>
fruition multiples as dreams become real <br>
for the first time since birth,  <br>
until I return to the knowledge-rich soil <br>
to cultivate my soul’s rebirth.
		</p>
	</div>



